README

-- 

in this file, we will discuss the some details of the objective-C programming language, which is the underlying language that provide the basic features. 

 
to use the GnuStep's Block extension, you may use the following compiler flags.  
 
 
 -fconstant-string-class=NSConstantString -fblocks -lobjc2 -lgnustep-base

If that is the CLang C front , you may use the following. 

clang -fblocks blocks-test.c -lBlocksRuntime


 
